Description: Complete seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The rear shows one side with one coil of basketry and another side with two coils of basketry suggesting that the piece was attached between the wall and the lid of a basket. At the front finger impressions and what looks like traces of smoothing the clay (?). An almost complete seal-impression of an oval scarab-like seal shows Hh, a seated figure with raised arms and a palm branch on each side (C11), underneath a simple nbw-sign.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
